# Main text

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
$PAR
True or false:
If a sequence of functions converges uniformly, then it converges pointwise.
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$q1 = RadioButtons([
"True",
"False",
],
"True",
);
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ $q1->buttons \}

$PAR
True or false:
If a sequence of functions converges pointwise, then it converges uniformly.
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$q2 = RadioButtons([
"True",
"False",
],
"False",
);
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ $q2->buttons \}

$PAR
True or false:
Suppose \(X \subset {\mathbb{R}}\) is finite and
\(f_n \colon X \to {\mathbb{R}}\) give a sequence of functions
that converges pointwise.  Then \($LB f_n $RB\) converges uniformly.
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$q3 = RadioButtons([
"True",
"False",
],
"True",
);
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ $q3->buttons \}

$PAR
True or false:
Suppose \(f_n \colon [a,b] \to {\mathbb{R}}\) are such that
\(f_n(x) \leq f_{n+1}(x)\) for all \(n \in {\mathbb{N}}\) and all \(x \in [a,b] .\)
Then \($LB f_n $RB\) converges pointwise.
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$q4 = RadioButtons([
"True",
"False",
],
"False",
);
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ $q4->buttons \}

$PAR
True or false:
Suppose \(f_n \colon [a,b] \to {\mathbb{R}}\) are bounded functions such that
\(f_n(x) \leq f_{n+1}(x)\) for all \(n \in {\mathbb{N}}\) and all \(x \in [a,b] .\)
Then \($LB f_n $RB\) converges pointwise.
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$q5 = RadioButtons([
"True",
"False",
],
"False",
);
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ $q5->buttons \}

$PAR
True or false:
Suppose \(f_n \colon [a,b] \to {\mathbb{R}}\) are such that
\(f_n(x) \leq f_{n+1}(x)\) for all \(n \in {\mathbb{N}}\) and all \(x \in [a,b] .\)
Suppose also that for each \(x \in [a,b]\) there is a \(B_x \in {\mathbb{R}}\) such that \(f_n(x) \leq B_x\)
for all \(n \in {\mathbb{N}}.\)
Then \($LB f_n $RB\) converges pointwise.
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

