\(f_n(x) \leq f_{n+1}(x)\) for all \(n \in {\mathbb{N}}\) and all \(x \in [a,b] .\)
Suppose also that there exists a \(B \in {\mathbb{R}}\)
such that \(f_n(x) \leq B\)
for all \(n \in {\mathbb{N}} \) and all \(x \in [a,b] .\)
Then \($LB f_n $RB\) converges pointwise.
$BR
END_TEXT
